•   { inv ∧ n ≠ N } S { inv(n+1) }

(1) S = ? // S = r:= E 

(2) E = ?

≡   Hoare triple

    inv ∧ n ≠ N ⇒ wp.(r:= E).(inv(n+1))

≡   Prove ⇒

    •   wp.(r:= E).(inv(n+1))

    (3) r = f.n
    
    (4) 0 ≤ n
    
    (5) n ≤ N

    (6) n ≠ N

    ≡   Assignment

        E = f.(n+1) ∧ 0 ≤ n+1 ∧ n+1 ≤ N

    ≡   Inequalities, using assumptions (4..6)

        E = f.(n+1)

    ■